{
  "texts": [
    "The corresponding testing sensor value is checked to determine if it satisfies the condition LB ≤ testsensorval ≤ UB.",
    "For time index 1 in TABLE 3, LIT101Diff is undefined.",
    "This is because computing a diff, i.e., current value -previous value, requires two consecutive (time indexed) LIT101 sensor values.",
    "For testing index 2, a diff exists.False condition, resulting in the baby-step method issuing an out of bounds warning event.",
    "The 6 baby-step bounds for LIT101 determined from training using the SWaT normal dataset are shown in Fig.7."
  ]
}